Overall Accuracy: 73%
5. Visualization Gallery
To gain insights into the model and dataset, several visualizations were generated:

- Feature Importance Plot – Highlights which features most influenced the predictions.
- Confusion Matrix Heatmap – Visualizes performance across crime categories.
- SMOTE Distribution Plot – Shows data balancing after applying SMOTE.
6. Prediction Example
An example input to the trained model demonstrates its real-world usability.

Example Input:
City: Pune
Victim Age: 25
Victim Gender: Female
Weapon Used: Blunt Object
Police Deployed: 5
Occur Year: 2025
Occur Month: 10
Occur Day: 3
Occur Weekday: 3 (Thursday)
Occur Hour: 14
Occur Minute: 30

Predicted Output: Other Crime
Prediction Probabilities: [0.205, 0.43, 0.045, 0.32]
7. Conclusion
This case study demonstrates how machine learning can effectively support law enforcement in identifying and classifying crime domains.

By combining Random Forest with SMOTE resampling, the model successfully mitigates data imbalance and achieves reliable accuracy.

Future Enhancements:
- Incorporate geospatial and socioeconomic data
- Apply hyperparameter tuning and feature selection
- Integrate real-time prediction dashboards
